task.summary: Set image/capture/preview size. Lots of comments.
Set up dummy unit tests: make sure that the unit tests run for a simple case.
Set up dummy unit tests: make sure that the unit tests run for a simple case.
Get control of camera frame rate - 5FPS and 7FPS work on the Nexus6, 15FPS allows the concurrent threads to increase until it blocks on "GC alloc". Refactor some configuration and processing.
Quick FPS change monitor based on recorded FPS and number of concurrent threads.
Start putting Help text in with the exact version number.

FPS under conrol: 1) calc Camera2 requested FPS increase/decrease toward target from current FPS (calculated from completion rate) and number of threads 1.1) button to calculate and apply FPS and clear performance log to get fresh data before next calculation 2) added check on number of threads at start of doInBackground
Put GrayF32 images into a re-use queue to avoid re-creating them on every thread execution. Refactor for readability.
Put GrayF32 images into a re-use queue to avoid re-creating them on every thread execution. Refactor for readability.
